# Antigravity Scanner

[![Python 3.9+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.9+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)
[![Code style: black](https://img.shields.io/badge/code%20style-black-000000.svg)](https://github.com/psf/black)
[![Ruff](https://img.shields.io/endpoint?url=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/astral-sh/ruff/main/assets/badge/v2.json)](https://github.com/astral-sh/ruff)

**High-performance codebase scanner and text extractor for LLM/RAG preparation.**

Scan massive repositories (100GB+), extract readable text content, and organize files with powerful tools—all while maintaining bounded memory usage and responsive UI.

## Features

### Core Capabilities
- **Multi-mode Scanning**: Single file, multi-file by extension, or chunked by size/token count
- **Incremental Scans**: Blake3/xxhash-based caching for fast re-scans
- **Smart Filtering**: `.scanignore` files (gitignore-style), binary detection, size limits, regex patterns
- **Text Extraction**: Code files, PDF, DOCX, archives (ZIP/TAR), optional OCR for images
- **Organization Toolkit**: Prefixer, Cleaner, Purger, Flattener, Pattern Mover, Duplicate Detector
- **Dual Interface**: Modern PyQt6 GUI + Full-featured CLI with rich output

### Performance
- **Streaming I/O**: Handle arbitrarily large files without OOM
- **Thread Pool**: Adaptive worker count based on system resources
- **Atomic Writes**: Safe output with rollback capability
- **Progress Tracking**: Real-time updates with ETA estimation

### Analytics & Insights
- File type breakdown (pie charts)
- Size distribution (treemaps)
- Scan history timeline
- Resource monitoring (CPU, RAM, I/O)

### AI Integration (Optional)
- LLM summarization hooks (Ollama local or OpenAI/Anthropic APIs)
- Token estimation for context window planning
- Smart chunking for RAG pipelines

## Installation

### From Source (Recommended for Development)

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-org/antigravity-scanner.git
cd antigravity-scanner

# Create virtual environment
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate

# Install with development dependencies
pip install -e ".[dev,analytics,extractors]"

# Install pre-commit hooks
pre-commit install
```

### Quick Install

```bash
pip install antigravity-scanner
```

### Optional Dependencies

```bash
# For analytics dashboard
pip install "antigravity-scanner[analytics]"

# For AI features
pip install "antigravity-scanner[ai]"

# For document extraction (PDF, DOCX, OCR)
pip install "antigravity-scanner[extractors]"

# All extras
pip install "antigravity-scanner[dev,analytics,ai,extractors]"
```

## Usage

### GUI Application

```bash
# Launch the graphical interface
antigravity-gui

# Or via Python module
python -m antigravity
```

### Command Line Interface

```bash
# Basic scan
antigravity scan /path/to/repo --output output.txt.gz

# Scan with filters
antigravity scan /path/to/repo \
    --include "*.py" "*.js" "*.md" \
    --exclude "node_modules" "dist" ".git" \
    --max-size 10MB \
    --output scan_result.txt

# Incremental scan (uses cache)
antigravity scan /path/to/repo --incremental --cache-dir ~/.antigravity/cache

# Chunked output (for large contexts)
antigravity scan /path/to/repo \
    --mode chunked \
    --chunk-size 4000 \
    --output-dir chunks/

# Organization tools
antigravity organize /path/to/files \
    --tool cleaner \
    --dry-run  # Preview changes without applying

# View scan history
antigravity history --limit 20 --format table

# Export analytics report
antigravity analytics /path/to/repo --report html --output report.html
```

### CLI Help

```bash
antigravity --help
antigravity scan --help
antigravity organize --help
```

## Configuration

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Description | Default |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `ANTIGRAVITY_CONFIG` | Path to config file | `~/.antigravity/config.toml` |
| `ANTIGRAVITY_LOG_LEVEL` | Logging level | `INFO` |
| `ANTIGRAVITY_CACHE_DIR` | Cache directory | `~/.antigravity/cache` |
| `ANTIGRAVITY_DB_PATH` | SQLite database path | `~/.antigravity/antigravity.db` |
| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | OpenAI API key (optional) | - |
| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Anthropic API key (optional) | - |

### Configuration File (TOML)

Create `~/.antigravity/config.toml`:

```toml
[general]
theme = "system"  # "light", "dark", "system"
language = "en"
max_workers = "auto"  # or integer

[scan]
default_mode = "multi"
chunk_size = 4000
chunk_overlap = 200
enable_incremental = true
follow_symlinks = false
max_file_size = "100MB"
exclude_patterns = [".git", "node_modules", "__pycache__", "*.pyc"]

[filters]
detect_binary = true
min_text_ratio = 0.7
encoding_detection = "chardet"

[output]
compression = "gzip"  # "none", "gzip"
atomic_writes = true
include_metadata = true

[ai]
provider = "ollama"  # "ollama", "openai", "anthropic"
model = "llama2"
api_base = "http://localhost:11434"

[logging]
level = "INFO"
file = "~/.antigravity/logs/antigravity.log"
rotation = "10MB"
backup_count = 5
```

### .scanignore Files

Create `.scanignore` files in directories to exclude patterns (gitignore syntax):

```gitignore
# Ignore node modules
node_modules/
vendor/

# Ignore build artifacts
*.pyc
__pycache__/
*.so
*.dll

# Ignore large data files
*.pkl
*.h5
data/*.csv

# Ignore secrets
.env
*.key
secrets/
```

## Architecture

```
antigravity-scanner/
├── src/antigravity/
│   ├── __init__.py          # Package init, version info
│   ├── __main__.py          # GUI entry point
│   ├── cli.py               # Typer CLI application
│   ├── core/                # Business logic (UI-agnostic)
│   │   ├── scanner.py       # Directory scanning engine
│   │   ├── writer.py        # Output writers (text, gzip, json)
│   │   ├── filters.py       # File filtering logic
│   │   ├── extractors/      # Format-specific extractors
│   │   │   ├── base.py
│   │   │   ├── code.py
│   │   │   ├── pdf.py
│   │   │   ├── docx.py
│   │   │   └── ocr.py
│   │   └── organizer/       # File organization tools
│   │       ├── base.py
│   │       ├── prefixer.py
│   │       ├── cleaner.py
│   │       ├── purger.py
│   │       ├── flattener.py
│   │       └── pattern_mover.py
│   ├── gui/                 # PyQt6 components
│   │   ├── app.py           # Main application window
│   │   ├── themes/          # Theme definitions
│   │   ├── views/           # Tab views
│   │   │   ├── primary.py
│   │   │   ├── advanced.py
│   │   │   ├── organizer.py
│   │   │   ├── history.py
│   │   │   └── settings.py
│   │   ├── widgets/         # Reusable widgets
│   │   └── dialogs/         # Modal dialogs
│   ├── models/              # SQLAlchemy ORM models
│   │   └── database.py
│   ├── services/            # Business services
│   │   ├── database.py      # DB connection & migrations
│   │   ├── history.py       # Scan history management
│   │   ├── settings.py      # Settings management
│   │   └── cache.py         # Incremental cache service
│   ├── schemas/             # Pydantic validation schemas
│   │   ├── config.py
│   │   ├── scan.py
│   │   └── organizer.py
│   └── utils/               # Utilities
│       ├── logging.py       # Structured logging
│       ├── paths.py         # Path utilities
│       ├── concurrency.py   # Thread pool helpers
│       └── platform.py      # Cross-platform helpers
├── tests/                   # Test suite
├── pyproject.toml           # Project configuration
├── .pre-commit-config.yaml  # Pre-commit hooks
└── README.md                # This file
```

## Development

### Running Tests

```bash
# Run all tests with coverage
pytest

# Run specific test module
pytest tests/test_scanner.py -v

# Run with coverage report
pytest --cov=src/antigravity --cov-report=html

# Run GUI tests (requires display)
pytest tests/gui/ -v
```

### Code Quality

```bash
# Format code
black src/ tests/

# Lint code
ruff check src/ tests/

# Type checking
mypy src/antigravity

# Run all checks
pre-commit run --all-files
```

### Building Executables

```bash
# Windows
pyinstaller AntigravityScanner.spec

# macOS
pyinstaller AntigravityScanner-macOS.spec

# Linux
pyinstaller AntigravityScanner-linux.spec
```

## Database Schema

The application uses SQLite with the following tables:

- **scan_records**: Completed scan metadata
- **scan_files**: Individual file tracking (for incremental scans)
- **scan_config_profiles**: Saved scan configurations
- **app_settings**: Application settings

Database location: `~/.antigravity/antigravity.db`

## Security Considerations

- **Path Traversal Protection**: All paths are normalized and validated
- **Output Directory Sandboxing**: Write operations restricted to allowed directories
- **Permission Checks**: Verify read/write permissions before operations
- **Binary Detection**: Magic byte analysis prevents processing non-text files
- **No External Calls**: Core scanning operates offline; AI features require explicit opt-in

## Troubleshooting

### Common Issues

**Issue**: "Permission denied" errors during scan  
**Solution**: Check file permissions or run with appropriate user privileges

**Issue**: High memory usage  
**Solution**: Reduce `--max-workers` or enable chunked mode

**Issue**: Slow incremental scans  
**Solution**: Clear cache with `antigravity cache clear` and rescan

**Issue**: GUI not starting on Linux  
**Solution**: Ensure PyQt6 is properly installed: `pip install --force-reinstall PyQt6`

### Logs

Logs are stored at `~/.antigravity/logs/antigravity.log`. Increase verbosity:

```bash
export ANTIGRAVITY_LOG_LEVEL=DEBUG
antigravity scan /path --verbose
```

